<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920304-0066</DOCNO><DOCID>920304-0066.</DOCID><HL>   Financing Business:   TransAlta Utilities Corp.</HL><DATE>03/04/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   T.TAU</CO><MS>UTILITIES (UTI)</MS><IN>ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)</IN><NS>SHAREHOLDER RIGHTS PLANS (SRP)</NS><RE>CANADA (CN)NORTH AMERICA (NME)</RE><LP>   TRANSALTA UTILITIES Corp. said it plans to raise 134.8million Canadian dollars (US$113.1 million) through a rightsoffering. Under the offering, each shareholder of theelectric utility of record March 17 will receive one rightfor every share held. A shareholder can exchange 12 rightsand C$11 to purchase one common share under the plan. Therights will expire April 14, the company said in Calgary,Alberta. TransAlta said proceeds will be used to repayshort-term debt. Richard McKinnon, vice president, finance,said that if all the rights are exercised, 12,250,000 newcommon shares could be issued, bringing shares outstanding to158 million. Toronto investment dealer Wood Gundy Inc. willlead the dealer group for the rights issue. In trading on theToronto Stock Exchange yesterday, the stock closed at C$12.75a share, unchanged.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>